summary:
A federal grand jury charged 31-year-old Ryan Wesley Routh from California with attempted assassination of President-elect Donald Trump and high-level officials. Prosecutors stated Routh planned to use a rifle at a Washington dinner event. The US Secret Service arrested him after discovering the plot. Trial proceedings are scheduled in federal court. This incident involves heightened security for US leaders.

The Trump administration imposed sanctions on a major Chinese oil refinery and 40 shipping companies for transporting Iranian oil, targeting Tehran's revenue used to fund militias. Chinese firms and Iranian oil exports face asset freezes and transaction bans, affecting global energy markets. Separately, a three-judge US Court of Appeals panel upheld a lower court ruling blocking Trump's executive order suspending asylum claims at the southern border, restoring processing for migrants from border states. In another policy move, the Justice Department authorized firing squads and single-drug lethal injections as federal execution methods, applying to death row inmates and enabling resumption of 13 paused cases.

The Trump administration dismissed all 24 members of the National Science Board, which oversees National Science Foundation grants, restructuring federal research funding decisions. Mexican special forces captured alleged Jalisco New Generation Cartel leader El Jardinero, a potential successor to El Mencho, in a ditch near Guadalajara, disrupting drug trafficking routes. Australia proposed legislation requiring Meta, Google, and TikTok to pay news publishers or face a 2.25 percent levy on Australian revenue. Medecins Sans Frontieres reported Israel restricts clean water access for 2.3 million Gaza Palestinians. SpaceX launched the Crew-10 mission Friday at 7:03 p.m. from Kennedy Space Center, sending four astronauts to the ISS to retrieve NASA astronauts Butch Wilmore and Suni Williams after nine months."}
